<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7621840>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Chloeia amphora Horst, 1910, non-type specimens (UF 4369). A. Dorsal view. B. Anterior end, dorsal view, after Shirlastain-A pigmentation. C. Chaetigers 10-12, dorsal view (left branchia of chaetiger 10 removed). D. Posterior end, ventral view. E. Another specimen, chaetiger 3, notochaeta (insets: notochaetal tips). F. Same, neurochaetal tips. G. Chaetiger 12, harpoon notochaetae. H. Same, neurochaetal tips. Scale bars: A, 1.5 mm; B, 0.5 mm; C, 0.4 mm; D, 0.7 mm; E, 110 μm; F, 70 μm; G, 160 μm; H, 40 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7621840/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7621842>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Chloeia bemisae sp. n., holotype (UF 4388).A. Dorsal view. B. Anterior end, dorsal view. C. Left lateral view. D. Paratype (UF 4388b), ventral view. E. Same, chaetiger 4, notochaetal tips. F. Same, neurochaetal tips. G. Chaetiger 11, harpoon notochaetae. H. Same, neurochaetae. Scale bars: A, 1.8 mm; B, 0.5 mm; C, 2.3 mm; D, 1.6 mm; E, 110 μm; F, 25 μm; G, 90 μm; H, 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7621842/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

